						<div class="commentEntry">
				<div class="commentDate">On December 12, 2011 at 6:53am</div>
				<div class="commentAuthor"><strong>Guillaume</strong> wrote:</div>
				<div class="commentBody"><p>So if I understand the Table 2 correctly, the optimal capacity to charge a Li-ion battery is 50% ?</p>

<p>100% * 500 cycles = 500 times full capacity<br />
50% * 1500 cycles = 750 times full capacity<br />
25% * 2500 cycles = 625 times full capacity<br />
10% * 4700 cycles = 470 times full capacity</p>

<p>Did I miss something ?</p></div>
